article.headline: E. Kentucky 70, Tenn.-Martin 51
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Mike Rose scored 18 points, including the first 10 of the second half, as Eastern Kentucky beat Tennessee Martin 70-51 Wednesday night. The Colonels (6-5, 3-0 Ohio Valley Conference) won for the fourth time in five games and made 11 3-pointers. Rose had four 3-pointers and three assists. Lester Hudson led Martin (5-6, 1-2) with 20 points, all in the second half. Djero Riedewald added 10. Eastern shot 54 percent from the field, including a 39 percent clip from 3-point range. Martin scored the first bucket of the game on a 3-pointer by Marquis Weddle, but the Colonels responded by scoring 14 unanswered points to take the lead for good. The Skyhawks narrowed the margin to 14-8 with 10 minutes left in the half, but Eastern outscored them 22-6 for a 36-14 halftime lead.
